Business Day 
Beyoncé Song Lifts Sales 33% at Red Lobster Chain

By THE ASSOCIATED PRESSFEB. 10, 2016



Continue reading the main story
Share This Page

Continue reading the main story








Photo






Beyoncé, center, in a scene from the video for her new song “Formation.”





The seafood restaurant chain Red Lobster said sales surged 33 percent on Sunday, compared with last year’s Super Bowl Sunday, after Beyoncé released a song, “Formation,” in which she sings about taking a romantic partner to the restaurant.“It’s clear that Beyoncé has helped create some Red Lobster fans,” Red Lobster’s chief, Kim Lopdrup, said in a statement. More conventional contributing factors for the rise in sales included relatively mild weather and a “Lobsterfest” promotion.The spotlight is a welcome change for Red Lobster, which was cast off by Darden Restaurants in 2014 after a long stretch of declining sales. The chain, which is now privately held by the investment firm Golden Gate Capital, said the Beyoncé song made Red Lobster a trending topic on Twitter for the first time.

